A judge has approved a plan to resolve concussion lawsuits brought by more than 5,000 former players that could cost the league $ 1billion over 65 years .
The deal comes after the league has been dogged for years hid the risks of repeated concussions in order to return players .
The NFL expects 6,000 of nearly 20,000 retired players to suffer from Alzheimer 's disease or moderate dementia someday .
The settlement would pay them about $ 190,000 on average .